node.text:
• My skincare routine these days is all about the #PowerOfHA 🙆🏻‍♀️ You ask why? Because a new way to mask is here with the L'Oreal Paris Hyaluronic Acid Plumping Fresh Mix Serum Mask! ❤️ #ad 

The mask is freshly mixed by you, this preserves the freshness and gives your skin a fresh boost of Hyaluronic Acid which is a superstar ingredient. 💁🏻‍♀️ The process is super simple as I've shown in the video and the mask itself is very light and breathable. I personally love to follow it up with the 1.5% Hyaluronic Acid Serum and a moisturizer. 

If you're looking for hydrated, plump and radiant skin just like me, I would highly recommend this! ✨

Shop the mask: https://amzn.to/3fFsOwj 

#AashnaMalani x @lorealparis #HyaluronicAcidMask

node.title: L’Oréal Paris HA Fresh Mix Serum Mask | Review

node.text: From discussing about what Mental Health means, to busting myths around it and breaking the stigma, we talk about the importance of mental health at length. This is so so close to my heart and I'm glad I could share this Live with @thebodyshopindia and @chhaya_psychologist to highlight that mental health is just as important, if not more than physical health. If you found this helpful, please share it with friends and family who might need to hear this! 🖤 #AashnaMalani x #TBS #TheBodyShopIndia #MentalHealthMatters

node.title: Mental Health Discussion ft. The Body Shop

node.text:
• #AashnaTalks | Be You. 🌸

Break the “tags”, break the stereotypes and make your own space in this world. You, as your unique self, are the most beautiful at your best potential so go ahead and just #BeYou.❄️ #AashnaMalani

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Aashna Malani 🧿 in Delhi, India with @ihollagram, @lorealparis, @aashnamalanii, @inbreakthrough, and @lorealindia. May be a closeup of 1 person, jewelry and text that says 'D'.

node.text:
• We‘ve all faced sexual harassment in public places and it’s appalling to me how many people choose to hide or ignore it. It’s time #WeStandUp and stop pretending like it didn’t happen because that only leads to self-doubt and it’s not our fault, it’s their responsibility to not do it. 

Our words and actions have the power to end street harassment, let’s together end sexual harassment in public places & #StandUpBecauseWeAreAllWorthIt 🙌🏻

I’m proudly supporting @lorealparis in this initiative and you too can get more information by Swiping up on my story. Learn what to do When you see it happen Or If it happens to you. 

#AashnaMalani x #LOrealParis #Hollaback @lorealparis @ihollagram @inbreakthrough @lorealindia

• Do you guys want to know my go-to regime for plumpy radiance? ❤️

I like to create moisture sandwich with the L'Oreal Paris Hyaluronic Acid Serum followed by HA Gel Cream. Layering them together makes HA more effective and gives me hydrated, plump and radiant looking skin every single day. 💁🏻‍♂️

So what are you waiting for? Upgrade to L'Oreal Paris Hyaluronic Acid range today! 😍

#AashnaMalani x #AD #PowerOfHA @lorealparis

• How to make 🥭🍹 at home! 

I absolutely love summers and mangoes, so decided to make this simple recipe using ingredients at home and it turned out delicious!! 🥭🍹 

You can store the concentrate in fridge for 30-40 days and enjoy it the whole month by just adding some ice, concentrate and cold water 🥰 

Let me know how this recipe turns out for you using #DIYwithAashna 💞 #AashnaMalani

node.text:
• Travelling and exploring India has been so therapeutic #throwback❤️ I couldn’t help but give in to this trend and share some of my favourite places I miss deeply (although couldn’t fit all) 😍

Life has changed so much but I’m so grateful for every experience I’ve cherished and I’m looking forward to better times soon. Do you guys want to see the international travel video too?😍 #AashnaMalani #VocalforLocal #TravelWithMe #ReelItFeelIt

node.text:
• I got vaccinated yesterday and I urge you to get your doses too. #DontWaitVaccinate! 🙏🏻 

Since so many of you asked me about after effects and if it was manageable, here’s my update after getting Covishield 👇🏻

Day 1: sore arm, headache and body ache, no fever (98.6 temp)

Day 2: sore arm, light headache and body ache, no fever (99.1 temp)

Day 3: sore arm, light headache and tiredness, no fever (98.3 temp)

Day 4: no vaccine effects

Let me know if you have any other questions and I’d be happy to answer them! #AashnaMalani #vaccinationdone✔️
